    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - WorkStar&#8482; Series Starting March 2007 - REMOVE AND INSTALL
        PROCEDURES - Fender Mounted Lights
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Fender Mounted Lights</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Clearance Light - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0901423" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901423.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Clearance Light</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CLEARANCE LIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. WIRE HARNESS CONNECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MOUNT SCREW</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The left side clearance light is shown in this procedure. Follow the same steps to remove the
                        right side clearance light.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the wire harness connector from the clearance light assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the mount screw and washer.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">While holding the clearance light assembly, depress and push the two mount retainer
                    clips (not shown in figure) through the mounting holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove clearance light assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the bulb:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Twist the socket counterclockwise on the back of the clearance light assembly and
                            disconnect.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Remove bulb from socket.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Clearance Light - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the bulb:</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Insert bulb into socket.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Connect socket to the back of the clearance light assembly and turn clockwise to lock.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align and insert the clearance light assembly in the mounting hole (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901423">Figure 43, Item 1</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install and tighten the washer and mount screw (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901423">Figure 43, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the wire harness connector (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901423">Figure 43, Item 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Turn Signal - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0901424" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901424.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Fender Mounted Turn Signal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TURN SIGNAL ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. NUT AND WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. WIRE HARNESS SOCKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. MOUNT PLATE</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The fender mounted turn signals install in place of the standard clearance lights and are
                        optional on all 7000 series trucks.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Twist the wire harness socket counterclockwise and remove the wire harness socket from
                    the turn signal assembly. The bulb can be removed from the wire harness socket for replacement.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two nuts, washers and the mount plate from the turn signal assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the turn signal assembly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Turn Signal - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align and install the turn signal assembly on the fender, amber side forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the mounting plate on the turn signal assembly and secure with two washers and
                    nuts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901424">Figure 44</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Ensure the bulb is properly installed into the wire harness socket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the wire harness socket to the turn signal assembly and twist clockwise to lock
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901424">Figure 44, Items 1 and 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Close and latch the hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
